  "texts": [
    "Edge devices refer to a range of hardware components that include local storage systems, broadcasting network controllers, routers, switches, Remote Access Points (RAP), Base Stations (BS), and hotspots.",
    "The MEC system enables a distributed environment by executing activities close to the end user.",
    "A variety of edge computing systems have been created, making use of open-source software and hardware, such as Software-Defined Networking (SDN) and Network Function Virtualization (NFV), to improve computing capacity and facilitate virtualization approaches 8.",
    "The current RPM system is vulnerable to various cyber threats or attacks.",
    "Therefore, there is a need for an e-health system that can effectively manage, process, and analyze patient-generated medical data while ensuring its accuracy and accessibility to authorized users."
  ]
